accessibility_text:
## "Organize, agitate, educate"

## \- Susan B. Anthony

[ ](https://www.susanbanthonybirthplace.com/visit-1)

## [VISIT](https://www.susanbanthonybirthplace.com/visit-1)

Plan your visit to the birth home of Susan B. Anthony, request a virtual tour, or schedule a group/school tour. 

[Learn More >](https://www.susanbanthonybirthplace.com/visit-1)

[ ](https://www.susanbanthonybirthplace.com/about)

## [ABOUT](https://www.susanbanthonybirthplace.com/about)

As the first home of Susan B. Anthony, the Museum's mission is to educate minds about Susan's life and efforts that left a lasting impact on America.

[Learn More >](https://www.susanbanthonybirthplace.com/about)

[ ](https://www.susanbanthonybirthplace.com/learn)

## [LEARN](https://www.susanbanthonybirthplace.com/learn)

Dive into the world of Quaker life, abolition, temperance, Restellism, suffrage, and Susan B. Anthony's part in it all. 

[Learn More >](https://www.susanbanthonybirthplace.com/learn)

[ ](https://www.susanbanthonybirthplace.com/support)

## [SUPPORT](https://www.susanbanthonybirthplace.com/support)

Become a member. See how your contribution can make a difference towards preserving this historic home.

[Learn More >](https://www.susanbanthonybirthplace.com/support)

## WHAT'S NEW

## Votes for Women: How Suffrage Sparked a Suffrage Revolution

Friday, June 20th

Susan B. Anthony Birthplace Museum 

This exhibit features a “Votes for Women” tea set, generously donated by Ventfort Hall Gilded Age Mansions...
